@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{consult-extras.el} extends @samp{consult}, the package that provides enhanced search and navigation commands built on Emacs' completing-read interface. While @samp{consult} ships with powerful commands like @code{consult-ripgrep} and @code{consult-locate}, it does not include directory-scoped variants or a way to toggle multiline matching on the fly.

This package fills those gaps with two groups of commands:

@itemize
@item
Directory-scoped search commands that restrict @samp{consult-ripgrep} and @samp{consult-locate} to the current directory, avoiding the need to specify a search root each time (@ref{Directory-scoped search}).
@item
An enhanced Org heading navigation command that widens the buffer and unfolds all headings before jumping, ensuring consistent results regardless of the buffer's visibility state (@ref{Org heading navigation}).
@end itemize

The package also provides a toggle for multiline ripgrep search (@ref{Multiline toggle}).

It depends on the @samp{paths} package for directory path definitions.

